message.content:
1. There were two arms in the study: PPV/CPA and PPV alone.
2. T cell responses were measured in both arms.
3. Vaccinated peptides were used in the study.
4. The PPV/CPA arm involved vaccinated peptides.
5. The PPV alone arm involved vaccinated peptides.
6. T cell responses to the vaccinated peptides in the PPV/CPA arm were measured.
7. T cell responses to the vaccinated peptides in the PPV alone arm were measured.
8. The T cell responses to the vaccinated peptides in the PPV/CPA arm tended to be greater than those in the PPV alone arm.
